# Template for hosts/llm/sshkey — the file referenced by
# users.users.root.openssh.authorizedKeys.keyFiles in configuration.nix.
#
# To use:
#   1. cp hosts/llm/sshkey.example hosts/llm/sshkey
#   2. Replace this file's contents (including these comments) with your
#      OpenSSH public keys, one per line, e.g.:
#
#        ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAA... you@your-laptop
#        ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAA... you@your-phone
#
#   3. sudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake .#llm
#
# Notes:
#   - hosts/*/sshkey is gitignored so your real keys never leak into git.
#   - sshd reads this file as authorized_keys, where '#' lines are ignored
#     so leaving comments in the real sshkey is harmless but messy.
#   - If sshkey is absent, the flake still evaluates (see lib.optional guard
#     in configuration.nix), but root won't accept any SSH logins.
